SIMPLE: lotion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lotion
<hw>Lo"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lotio</ets>,
fr. <ets>lavare</ets>, <ets>lotum</ets>, to wash: cf. F.
<ets>lotion</ets>. See <er>Lave</er> to wash.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
washing, especially of the skin for the purpose of rendering it
fair.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A liquid preparation for bathing the skin, or an
injured or diseased part, either for a medicinal purpose, or for
improving its appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loto</ent>⟦br⟧
